3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of a non-blind learning-based SR result to guide the estimation process. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the estimation of a nonparametric blur-kernel, which can be seen as an inverse problem in information theory. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of numerical optimization techniques to solve the functional to be minimized.
